                        <additions>
                            <list>
                                <item xml:id="a1">
                                    <desc type="Condemnation"/>
                                    <locus target="#51v"/>
                                    <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                                    <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                                    <p>The note excommunicates whoever sells the book for starvation or poverty and whoever steals it.</p>
                                </item>
                                <item xml:id="a2">
                                    <desc type="OwnershipNote"/>
                                    <locus target="#51v"/>
                                    <q xml:lang="en">"This book belongs to Ksâda Qâl, whose wife is Biruthâwit, whose father is Afa-Christôs, and whose mother is .... The scribe 
                                        is Thabor".</q>
                                    <note>The note states that the book belongs to <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10769KesadaQ">Ksâda Qâl</persName>. His wife 
                                        <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10770BirutH">Biruthâwit</persName> and his father <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10771AfaKre">Afa-Christôs</persName> 
                                        are also mentioned. The note also mentions <persName role="scribe" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10768Tabor">Thabor</persName> as the scribe.</note> 
                                </item>
                                <item xml:id="a3">
                                    <desc type="CalendaricNote"/>
                                    <locus target="#142r"/>
                                    <q xml:lang="gez">ዘአርዓያ፡ ዘሳቤላ፡ ፱ፀሐይ፡ ወ፩ዘመን፡ ፯፻ወ፸ወ፰። ወታሰዓይሰ፡ ዘመን፡ ዓመታቲሁ። ፯፻ወ፸ወ፯። ዘሳቤላ፡ ቀመር፡ ፰፻ወ፯፻ወ፩ለ፩፡ ዘመን፡ ፰፻፡ ዓመት። ዝዕዝራ፡ 
                                        ቀመር። ፵ወ፱ወ፩ቀመር፡ ፻ወ፵ወ፫ዓመት። ዘሄኖክ፡ ቀመር፡ ፲ለ፩ዘመን፡ ፯፻ዓመት። ለእግዚአቭሔር፡ ዕለታቲሁ፡ ፯ወበኀቤነሰ፡ ዕለታት። ፪፻፼ወ፭፼ወ፹፻።</q>
                                    <q xml:lang="en"/>
                                    <note>The note records the number of cycles and years per cycle according to the computation systems of Sibyl, Ezra and Enoch.</note>
                                    <listBibl type="text">
                                        <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/FVDGF5SX"><seg type="journalArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Schleifer1910Weisheit"/><title level="a">Die Weisheit der Sibylle</title><title level="j">Wiener Zeitschrift für die Kunde des Morgenlandes</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Joel</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Schleifer</t:surname></author><date>1910</date><biblScope unit="volume">24</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">33-50</biblScope><citedRange unit="page">3a-3b</citedRange></bibl>
                                    </listBibl>
                                </item>
                                <item xml:id="a4">
                                    <desc>List of canonical books</desc>
                                    <locus target="#142"/>
                                    <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                                    <q xml:lang="en"/>
                                    <note>The note lists the books of the Old and the New Testament according to the Ethiopian canon. The total number of books is also provided.</note>
                                </item>
                                <item xml:id="a5">
                                    <desc type="CalendaricNote"/>
                                    <locus target="#142"/>
                                    <q xml:lang="en">"The days since Adam until the end of the world (are) 2.556.750; one cycle (has) 194.180 days; (the number of) cycles of 
                                        Adam (is) 13, each cycle (has) 532 years. The cycles of the Jubilees (are) 142 seven-year-cycles, each cycle (has) 42 years".</q>
                                    <note>The note records the number of days since Adam until the end of the world, the number of days and years per cycle according to the 
                                        computation system of Adam.</note>
                                </item>
                                <item xml:id="a6">
                                    <desc type="Poem"/>
                                    <locus target="#143"/>
                                    <note>Rhymed poem in honor of Our Lady Mary, incomplete.</note>
                                </item>
                            </list>
                        </additions>
